articles.content:
The junior college shall receive a letter of consent, as well as other relevant documents, from the applicant, to undertake examination through his or her overseas academic credentials,
Items which the junior college must examine concerning the applicant’s school abroad, or for which a written request for assistance must be submitted to the Republic of China’s overseas missions and offices in examining the applicant’s overseas academic credentials, are as follows:
1. Admission requirements;
2. Term of study;
3. Curriculum undertaken;
4. Whether or not the school is recognized by the competent authority of the foreign government concerned, or a dedicated educational accreditation entity indicated by the government; and
5. Other necessary items.
